 :tx/rationale "MINOR-2: LiveStore refresh has TOCTOU window [LOW, from FULL_AUDIT F-CONC-002]. refresh_if_needed() checks has_new_external_txns() via directory mtime, then reads new transaction files. Between check and read, another agent could write additional transactions that are missed. Classic TOCTOU. Mitigated: daemon holds store in memory; CLI refreshes before every command; content-addressed files are immutable so missed file caught on next refresh. Window is short (one command invocation). SOLUTION: Document as known behavior. No fix needed at current scale. At multi-agent scale, consider inotify-based watching or lockfile coordination. VERIFICATION: Documentation only. DEPENDENCIES: Will matter more when AUDIT-LOOP-2 (multi-agent coordination) is implemented."
